title: BugMeNot
description: BugMeNot is an Internet service that provides usernames and passwords to let Internet users bypass mandatory free registration on websites.

content.heading: Excellent for sites with annoying "login required" to view stuff
paragraphs: Many sites require you to register just to see a simple video or read a review... etc. Even if this registration is free if you stumble on a site that you are unlikely to visit again, creating yet another registration is a haste. BugMeNot.com will help you quickly bypass the login of web sites that require compulsory registration and/or the collection of personal/demographic information. The service is quite good as you only have to enter the site you need to log into and some other user would have shared credentials.

title: You.com
description: You.com is a search engine that summarizes the best parts of the internet for you, without ads.

content.heading: You.com is a search engine that summarizes the best parts of the internet for you, without ads and with great privacy.
paragraphs: Our AI will help you find the most relevant results from the web and apps that you can sort and prioritize for an optimum search experience.
We believe that you should control your search: your privacy, results, and time.
WHAT KIND OF SEARCH ENGINE IS YOU.COM?
Private: We don’t store any sensitive data. The only data we store is used to improve your search and never sold or distributed to third parties.

Customized: Signing in to You.com will give you control over what types of websites you want to see in your results. Over time, search results get better and better with the help of AI and your preferences.

Summarized: Websites and sources are presented as “Apps” on the search results to discover answers at a glance, dive deep into specific findings, or take action directly from search results. The novel interface enables both vertical and horizontal scroll to see more with fewer clicks.

title: Core.ac.uk
description: CORE is the world’s largest aggregator of open access research papers from repositories and journals

paragraphs: CORE is the world’s largest aggregator of open access research papers from repositories and journals.
CORE harvests research papers from such as institutional and subject repositories, and open access and hybrid journals.
CORE currently contains 223M open access articles collected from 11K data providers around the world.

We provide solutions for content management, discovery and scalable machine access to research. Our services support a wide range of stakeholders, specifically researchers, the general public, academic institutions, developers, funders and companies from a diverse range of sectors including but not limited to innovators, AI technology companies, digital library solutions and pharma.
It is a not-for-profit service dedicated to the open access mission. We serve the global network of repositories and journals by increasing the discoverability and reuse of open access content.
